messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Acceptable HTTP methods (based on code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The deleteEmployee(...) method in ManagerController is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE)
  which defines the full path and explicitly maps only the DELETE method for that path.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix to the path, so the path used is exactly the value given on the method.
- No other method in this controller maps to "/printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}", and no mapping without a specific RequestMethod exists for this path, so only DELETE is acceptable according to the source code.
- Per your instruction to base acceptability on the code (not runtime framework behavior), implicit framework support for HEAD/OPTIONS/TRACE is not assumed; they are marked false because they are not explicitly mapped.
